      "message": "Consider `std::variant\u003cStatement*, std::unique_ptr\u003cStatement\u003e*\u003e` as this class seems to basically be a spin on `variant`.\n\nIf variant doesn\u0027t work for you, consider replacing the `void*` with a `union { Statement*, std::unique_ptr\u003cStatement\u003e* }` to ease casting.\n\nIn my past project, we had a class called \"OptionallyOwned\" which might actually be interesting to you (although I don\u0027t think it could be plugged in here as-is, it might be close). If you set the deleter function on a std::shared_ptr appropriately, you can model different ownership semantics on a single shared_ptr type. It\u0027s really handy. PTAL if you are curious:\n\nhttp://google3/analytics/collection/server/golfe_injection.h?l\u003d93\u0026rcl\u003d201376600",
